{"title":"Litespeed Debuts Lightweight, Shapely New Toscana Gravel Bike","link":"https://bikerumor.com/litespeed-debuts-lightweight-shapely-new-toscana-gravel-bike/","date":1695815685000,"content":"<p><img width=\"2048\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Action-1.jpg\" alt=\"new litespeed toscana titanium gravel bike being ridden\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Action-1.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Action-1-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Action-1-800x450.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Action-1-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Action-1-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Action-1-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Action-1-400x225.jpg 400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Action-1-1200x675.jpg 1200w\" /></p>\n<p>Using the same house-made 6/4 titanium top tube as their ultralight Spezia road frame, the new Litespeed Toscana claims to be the lightest production titanium gravel bike on the market.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It shares the same size-specific tubing and tighter tolerances for tube wall thickness, too. And the insides of the head tube and bottom bracket are machined to remove weight. The result is a claimed frame weight of just 1,240g in size medium. That’s for the Toscana FI (Fully Integrated) model, and there’s a base model with standard cable routing, too. Let’s take a look…</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Toscana Frame Details</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-FI-Top-Tube-Overview.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1191\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-FI-Top-Tube-Overview.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of litespeed toscana titanium gravel bike top tube\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-FI-Top-Tube-Overview.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-FI-Top-Tube-Overview-297x177.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-FI-Top-Tube-Overview-800x476.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-FI-Top-Tube-Overview-120x71.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-FI-Top-Tube-Overview-768x457.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-FI-Top-Tube-Overview-1536x915.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Toscana’s frame features go well beyond the actual material, but the top tube is worth highlighting. Unlike most tubes, this one’s folded from a sheet of 6/4 ti, which lets them fine tune the ride quality.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Frame-Dropped-Chainstay-Side-View.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"884\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Frame-Dropped-Chainstay-Side-View.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of litespeed toscana titanium gravel bike bottom bracket and downtube\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Frame-Dropped-Chainstay-Side-View.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Frame-Dropped-Chainstay-Side-View-297x131.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Frame-Dropped-Chainstay-Side-View-800x354.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Frame-Dropped-Chainstay-Side-View-120x53.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Frame-Dropped-Chainstay-Side-View-768x339.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Frame-Dropped-Chainstay-Side-View-1536x679.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>A triaxially ovalized downtube has a partial teardrop shape to “aerodynamically shield the water bottle” before widening at the BB to maximize torsional stiffness.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Frame-Dropped-Chainstay-Rear-View.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Frame-Dropped-Chainstay-Rear-View.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of litespeed toscana titanium gravel bike chainstays\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Frame-Dropped-Chainstay-Rear-View.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Frame-Dropped-Chainstay-Rear-View-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Frame-Dropped-Chainstay-Rear-View-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Frame-Dropped-Chainstay-Rear-View-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Frame-Dropped-Chainstay-Rear-View-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Frame-Dropped-Chainstay-Rear-View-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Frame-Dropped-Chainstay-Rear-View-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The dropped driveside chainstay also creates more tire clearance, up to 700×48 gravel tires, while still allowing 2x gravel drivetrains.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-FI-Top-tube-Seat-tube-Intersect.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-FI-Top-tube-Seat-tube-Intersect.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of litespeed toscana titanium gravel bike seat stays\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-FI-Top-tube-Seat-tube-Intersect.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-FI-Top-tube-Seat-tube-Intersect-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-FI-Top-tube-Seat-tube-Intersect-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-FI-Top-tube-Seat-tube-Intersect-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-FI-Top-tube-Seat-tube-Intersect-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-FI-Top-tube-Seat-tube-Intersect-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-FI-Top-tube-Seat-tube-Intersect-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The seatstays land on the sides of the top tube. They say this wider stance adds lateral stiffness without giving up titanium’s signature ride quality, and it adds tire clearance.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-UDH-Dropout.jpg\"><img width=\"1758\" height=\"1218\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-UDH-Dropout.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of litespeed toscana titanium gravel bike dropouts\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-UDH-Dropout.jpg 1758w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-UDH-Dropout-297x206.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-UDH-Dropout-800x554.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-UDH-Dropout-120x83.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-UDH-Dropout-768x532.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-UDH-Dropout-1536x1064.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The dropouts are slightly relieved to save a few more grams and fit a UDH for future compatibility. Both models are offered with Di2- or AXS-specific designs, but you can order them with mechanical shift cable routing. That gives you the full range of gravel drivetrains, including the latest <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/sram-apex-is-now-1x12-with-eagle-xplr-axs-mechanical-options/\">SRAM Apex XPLR</a> and <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/shimano-grx-12-speed-mechanical/\">Shimano GRX</a> groups, not to mention Campy Ekar.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Toscana Pricing &amp; Options</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-FSA-Config-Profile.jpg\"><img width=\"1756\" height=\"1043\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-FSA-Config-Profile.jpg\" alt=\"litespeed toscana titanium gravel bike shown from side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-FSA-Config-Profile.jpg 1756w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-FSA-Config-Profile-297x176.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-FSA-Config-Profile-800x475.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-FSA-Config-Profile-120x71.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-FSA-Config-Profile-768x456.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-FSA-Config-Profile-1536x912.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The FI model uses a larger diameter head tube with their own carbon fork and the FSA ACR cockpit to hide all cables and wires. An ENVE InRoute fork/bar/stem upgrade option is also available. These models use a threaded T47 bottom bracket and are the lightest option. Bikes start at $7,550, and framesets are $4,550.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-3-4-Angle.jpg\"><img width=\"1506\" height=\"1093\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-3-4-Angle.jpg\" alt=\"litespeed toscana titanium gravel bike with standard cable routing\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-3-4-Angle.jpg 1506w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-3-4-Angle-297x216.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-3-4-Angle-800x581.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-3-4-Angle-120x87.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-3-4-Angle-768x557.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For those who like to keep it simpler (or save a few bucks), a non-FI model has standard internal routing. These start at $6,899 and come with a PF30 bottom bracket shell, but you can upgrade to T47. Claimed frame weight for this standard version is 1,355g, which is still pretty light for a titanium frame. Frameset is $4,295.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Environmental-2.jpg\"><img width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Environmental-2.jpg\" alt=\"litespeed toscana titanium gravel bike leaning against a wall\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Environmental-2.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Environmental-2-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Environmental-2-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Environmental-2-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Environmental-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Environmental-2-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Litespeed-Toscano-Environmental-2-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Choose from standard vinyl decals or their TiDize color anodization and etching for a more custom look. Frames come in XS/S/M/ML/L/XL sizes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://litespeed.com/collections/toscano\" target=\"_blank\">Litespeed.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/litespeed-debuts-lightweight-shapely-new-toscana-gravel-bike/\">Litespeed Debuts Lightweight, Shapely New Toscana Gravel Bike</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"138fd3e2e7eca252e8a6b2bc5dbd468413b6f3c435744c79b0672669d2e8887a","category":"Cycling"}